# OpenTelemetry Instrumentation Notes

Application: `{{ app.name }}`
Resolved OTEL service name: `{{ service_name }}`

Instrumentation depends on the application language, framework, and runtime. `k8s-forge` does not modify application code, does not add auto-instrumentation, does not inject sidecars, and does not create mutation webhooks.

## Useful Semantic Conventions

Useful attributes for the lab:

```text
service.name={{ service_name }}
deployment.environment=local
k8s.namespace.name={{ app.namespace }}
k8s.pod.name=<pod-name>
http.route=/weather
http.method=GET
http.status_code=200
```

For FastAPI or similar Python applications, instrumentation is usually configured in the application dependencies and startup code, then exported through OTLP to a collector.

## Validation Mindset

A generated dashboard or TraceQL query only becomes useful when the application emits spans and the collector forwards those spans to a backend such as Tempo.
